				"The Commodore Plus/4 is a^",
"home computer released by^",
"Commodore International in^",
"1984. The 'Plus/4' name refers^",
"to the four-application ROM^",
"resident office suite (word^",
"processor, spreadsheet,^",
"database, and graphing);^",
"it was billed as 'the^",
"productivity computer with^",
"software built-in'.^",
"Internally, the Plus/4^",
"shares the same basic^",
"architecture as the lower-^",
"end Commodore 16 and 116^",
"models, and is able to use^",
"software and peripherals^",
"designed for them. However,^",
"it is not compatible with^",
"the well-established Commodore^",
"64. While the Plus/4 had some^",
"success in Europe, it was a^",
"failure in the United States,^",
"where it was derided as the^",
"'Minus/60'.^"
